        "title": "Finding a way to parse multi-type JSON field",
        "body": "<p>We have a JSON-answer from server, where we have array of byte arrays, but there is also can be a \"None\" string value instead of empty array. Example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>{'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'id': 31, 'result': {\"bytes_arrays\": [[21,99,165,243,25,210,14,121,120,39,22,102,59],[22,32,42,54,65,65,76,87],None]}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In my class I usually write something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonProperty(\"bytes_arrays\")\n    private List&lt;byte[]&gt; mArraysList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>but of course, we'll have a parsing error for the last element with \"None\" value, because it's a string.<\/p>\n\n<p>Are there any ways to extract multi-type field in this JSON? We use Jackson.<\/p>\n",
